SPAN 4390 - The Contemporary Spanish American Novel
Study and analysis of works by major Spanish American novelists from
the period of the Mexican Revolution to the present. Emphasis placed on
themes and narrative technique in novels by writers such as Azuela,
Bombal, Rulfo, Fuentes, Garcia Marquez, Vargas Llosa, Poniatowska
and others. Taught in Spanish.
Prerequisite: CI.
